13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 396.3b of Title 59, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. The term "assistant funeral director" as herein used means a
18 person who assists a duly Oklahoma licensed funeral director in one
19 or more of the principal functions of funeral directing, and is
20 actively engaged in such work. An assistant funeral director must
21 be an employee of the funeral director-in-charge under whom the
22 employee is registered, and shall be a person to whom the funeral
23 director-in-charge delegates the responsibility of conducting
24
